      "side": 1,
      "message": "Disclaimer: I confess that I didn\u0027t fully read and understand the Spanner query discussed in the bug.\n\nmetric:state is to track the state of the expired invocation before the enforcement by deadlineenforcer.\n\nMy understanding is that this deadlineenforcer finalizes all the invocations with NON-finalized state, which includes\n- STATE_UNSPECIFIED\n- ACTIVE\n- FINALIZING\n\nFor example, an invocation could be set with FINALIZING and then abandoned due to a bug somewhere. Or, deadlineenforcer found an invocation with STATE_UNSPECIFIED, which shouldn\u0027t happen but maybe.\n\nI believe that the above scenarios will unlikely or shouldn\u0027t happen. However, if it\u0027s easy to report in the metric w/o extra costs, then I\u0027d like to see the info. Please correct me if I\u0027m totally wrong.",
